Christmas carols: multi-lingual, with chords, analyzed using Data Science

https://rpubs.com/ivim/noel (https://gorodnichy.github.io/noel)

Merry Christmas, tout le monde !

Voici sont les meilleures chansons de Noël et d’hiver for holiday season - in English, en français, and other languages - with chords and analyzed using data science techniques. The image below shows the graphical representation of the result - the most frequent words used to describe the holiday spirit in each language.

Figure 1: Data representation of Christmas songs in this booklet: English vs. French versions of the same songs


Songs are organized by the language origin: with those having multiple language versions appearing first, followed by New Year songs and other winter songs. Less known songs are accompanied by links to listen them on SoundCloud.

A pdf version of this document for printing or reading with e-reader is available here. Enjoy!

Other resources

List of Christmas Carols in wikipedia

Chord notation

“|” or blank indicate the end of measure, “||” - end of line, and indent - new melody part or refrain. H is Si/Ti major chord (B in standard notation) and B is Si/Ti flat major chord (Bb in standard notation). The rest follows the standard chord notation.

Contributions and corrections welcome! Email them to dg @ ivim.ca or fork the source github repo

Credits

This book is generated automatically from the R Markdown script in RStudio. The source is at GitHub.
The lyrics is analyzed using R. The chords and data analysis are provided by Dmitry Gorodnichy.
